description: Id of the run that completed the task
name: runId

description: Result of the sub component execution.
name: result

description: Identifier for a group of tasks scheduled together with this task. Generally, all tasks related to a single event such as a version-control push or a nightly build have the same taskGroupId. This property defaults to taskId if it isn't specified. Tasks with taskId equal to the taskGroupId are, by convention, decision tasks.
name: taskGroupId

description: Unique task identifier, this is UUID encoded as URL-safe base64 and stripped of = padding.
name: taskId

description: Unique identifier for a worker-type within a specific provisioner.
name: workerType

description: Date-time at which this run was scheduled, ie. when the run was created in state pending.
name: scheduled

description: Date-time at which this run was claimed, ie. when the run changed state from pending to running. This property is only present after the run has been claimed.
name: started

description: Date-time at which this run was resolved, ie. when the run changed state from running to either completed, failed or exception. This property is only present after the run as been resolved.
name: resolved

description: E-mail of person who caused this task, e.g. the person who did hg push. The person we should contact to ask why this task is here
name: owner

description: Treeherder live log file name (artifact, test, source code etc...)
name: file

description: Data nesting level, use to avoid double counting
name: level
